 article on the house by renowned poet John Ashbery. Illustrated with a generous selection of photographs taken over the years by the artist and his many visitors, this is an invaluable and intimate record of Ireland’s best-known work. 500 Capp Street is essential reading for anyone interested in the artistic and cultural history of the San Francisco Bay Area and the California conceptual art movement.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArtistsxHomes and hauntszCaliforniazSan Francisco. 0aConceptual artzCaliforniazSan Francisco. 4aAmerican. 4aArt. 4aGeneral. 7aART / American / General.2bisacsh1 aAshbery, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAshbery, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLewallen, Constance M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewallen, Constance M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aReynolds, Jock, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReynolds, Jock, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWilmans, Carlie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilmans, Carlie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052028028140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035581140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520355811423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520355811/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles